paper_title.ja: アンボンドＰＣ圧着工法によるエネルギー吸収型高復元性部材の荷重－変形関係に関する実験的検討
paper_title.en: EXPERIMENTAL STUDY FOR LOAD-DEFLECTION CHARACTERISTICS OF PRECAST PRESTRESSED FLEXURAL MEMBERS WITH UNBONDED TENDON AND MILD STEEL

description.ja: This paper describes precast prestressed concrete flexural members, in which a combination of unbonded post 'tensioning (PT) steel and bonded mild-steel is used. The unbonded PT steels are designed not to yield during seismic excitations, so as not to decrease a self-centering force. On the other hand, the bonded mild steels are intentionally designed to yield in order to dissipate energy. Tests on eight cantilever precast prestressed concrete flexural members are conducted to evaluate the mechanical characteristics. The test result shows that the members have very little residual displacement and have enough energy dissipations under severe earthquakes.

paper_title.ja: 丸鋼ＰＣ鋼棒圧着型片持ちＰＣ梁の荷重－変形関係のマクロモデルによる推定
paper_title.en: ESTIMATION OF LOAD-DEFORMATION CHARACTERISTICS USING PROPOSAL MACRO-MODEL FOR CANTILEVER PRECAST PC BEAMS ASSEMBLED BY ROUND PC TENDON

description.en: The authors propose a method by which to infer the load-deformation characteristics in the ultimate region of PC beams assembled by compressing to columns with round PC tendons. The conclusions are as described below. 1) Under the assumed appropriate deformation conditions, draw out of the PC tendons is computed on the basis of the bond characteristics of PC tendons, and a macro model which enables rotational deformations to be obtained is proposed. 2) the analysis results thus obtained about load-deformation characteristics of beams are in good agreement with the experimental results, and 3) in the aforesaid load-deformation characteristics, strains at extreme fibers of concrete and depth of neutral axis can be estimated with sufficient accuracy.
